        <content type="html" xml:base="https://aw2.help/builds/alac-condi-mirage/">&lt;h2 id=&quot;notes&quot;&gt;Notes&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The concept behind Alacrity Condition Mirage is that you want to use an Ambush attack, specifically &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40184&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Chaos Vortex, as much as possible, and how you get an Ambush attack is by dodging, or picking up Mirage Mirrors. Your next auto attack will be an Ambush after dodging or picking up a Mirage Mirror. This is especially important as it is designed to be a support build, and you will give Alacrity through your Ambush attacks.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this build Mirage Mirrors will be generated by &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40200&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; False Oasis and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;41065&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crystal Sands. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40200&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; False Oasis drops the Mirror where you&#x27;re standing, but &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;41065&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crystal Sands drops the Mirror where you&#x27;re aiming, and you want to always aim &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;41065&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crystal Sands inside the hitbox of the boss to ensure all of its hits land. You can use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45449&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Jaunt, which is a shadowstep, to pick it up.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ambush attacks also provide high uptime of both Might and Fury for your subgroup.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
